description.narrative: In 2019, joint efforts of UNICEF, WHO, GAVI and Government enabled to strengthen routine immunization in terms of cold chain, vaccine supply and reach every child. As result, vaccine coverage increased for all antigens. Vaccine coverage of DTP3 increased from 75 per cent in 2018 to 79 per cent as of October 2019.The equity focus is illustrated by the decrease of the number of low-performance districts (coverage vaccine less than 50 percent) from nine to five, a reduction of 55 per cent. | Status:Met | As-of Date:10/02/2020
